55.1	Nagarjuna	Nagarjuna	Acharya Nāgārjuna was an important Buddhist teacher and philosopher. Along with his disciple Āryadeva, he is credited with founding the Mādhyamaka school of Mahāyāna Buddhism. The Mādhyamaka school was in turn transmitted to China under the name of the Sānlùn School (Ch. 三論宗, "Three Treatise School").	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/Nagarjuna_at_Samye_Ling_Monastery.JPG/200px-Nagarjuna_at_Samye_Ling_Monastery.JPG
